{"schema_version": 2, "source_hash": "2684d4a1447fca9d", "candidate": {"id": "cand-017", "name": "Chloe Oduya", "raw_cv": "CHLOE ODUYA\nchloe.oduya@email.com | London, UK\n\nDATA ENGINEER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nData engineer with 3 years of experience building analytics pipelines in retail and e-commerce. Proficient in Python and SQL with growing skills in dbt and Snowflake. Strong collaborator with product and analytics teams.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nData Engineer \u2014 ASOS, London (2022\u2013present)\n- Built and maintained Python ETL pipelines feeding the product recommendations engine\n- Migrated 10 legacy SQL scripts to dbt models on Snowflake\n- Developed Airflow DAGs for daily product catalogue refresh\n\nData Analyst \u2014 Farfetch, London (2021\u20132022)\n- Built dashboards and SQL queries for the logistics operations team\n\nSKILLS\nPython, SQL, dbt, Snowflake, Airflow (basic), BigQuery, Looker, Git\n\nEDUCATION\nBSc Information Management \u2014 City, University of London (2018\u20132021)\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nBritish citizen (Nigerian heritage)", "raw_linkedin": "Data engineer at ASOS building the data pipelines behind product recommendations and catalogue management. Three years in the role, developing fast. Strong Python and SQL, growing dbt and Snowflake skills. London-based, right to work, happy to be in office. Looking to make my next move into a more technically demanding environment \u2014 ideally financial services or a high-growth scale-up.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Chloe, thanks for coming in. You're coming from e-commerce \u2014 what appeals about fintech?\n\nChloe: The data quality requirements are so much higher. At ASOS if a product attribute is wrong it's a minor customer experience issue. In fintech, data errors have regulatory and financial consequences. I want to work in a domain where accuracy really matters and where the data engineering standards are correspondingly high.\n\nInterviewer: Your dbt experience is relatively limited \u2014 10 models versus what we're running at 200+. How would you approach the learning curve?\n\nChloe: I'm confident in the fundamentals and I learn fast. I'd expect to spend the first month or two contributing to existing models while I absorb the patterns, then gradually take on more ownership. I've read up on the staging/intermediate/mart pattern and I'm building practice projects.\n\nInterviewer: Office \u2014 five days at Canary Wharf?\n\nChloe: Absolutely fine. I live in Peckham, so it's straightforward.\n\nInterviewer: Salary?\n\nChloe: I'm at \u00a352,000 currently. I'm looking for \u00a360\u201365,000 given the domain change and technical step up.", "years_experience": 3.0, "skills": ["Python", "SQL", "dbt", "Snowflake", "Airflow", "BigQuery", "Looker", "Git"], "industries": ["retail", "e-commerce", "fintech"], "seniority_level": "mid", "management_experience": false, "education_level": "bachelor", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.82, "culture_fit_score": 0.78, "constraints": [{"id": "b2b65be3", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Current salary is \u00a352,000", "canonical_key": "salary_current", "value": 52000.0, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "b6914c6e", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Seeking salary increase to \u00a360\u201365,000 following domain change and technical step up", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 60000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.93, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "e9f1bbd4", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Seeking salary range of \u00a360\u201365,000", "canonical_key": "salary_max", "value": 65000.0, "operator": "max", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.93, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "42cf8123", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Comfortable with five days per week in office at Canary Wharf; lives in Peckham", "canonical_key": "office_days_per_week", "value": 5.0, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.96, "currency": null}, {"id": "ab411d93", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "work_authorization", "description": "British citizen with right to work in UK", "canonical_key": "work_authorization", "value": "British citizen", "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98, "currency": null}, {"id": "3a11173e", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "career", "description": "Seeking role in financial services or high-growth scale-up; motivated by higher data quality standards and regulatory implications", "canonical_key": "industry_preference", "value": ["financial services", "high-growth scale-up"], "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.9, "currency": null}, {"id": "b488b62b", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "technical", "description": "Looking to move into a more technically demanding environment with higher data engineering standards", "canonical_key": "technical_challenge", "value": "more technically demanding environment", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.88, "currency": null}], "discipline": "other"}, "embedding": [0.040679931640625, 0.0031223297119140625, 0.054595947265625, 0.002960205078125, 0.0181427001953125, 0.032440185546875, 0.015533447265625, 0.0309906005859375, -0.038970947265625, -0.003871917724609375, 0.00534820556640625, -0.0219573974609375, -0.0498046875, -0.016357421875, 0.040802001953125, 0.0755615234375, -0.0164794921875, -0.034576416015625, -0.0125274658203125, 0.0170440673828125, 0.0021457672119140625, 0.027130126953125, -0.01146697998046875, 0.036590576171875, 0.0197601318359375, -0.01297760009765625, -0.0281982421875, -0.0022144317626953125, -0.035736083984375, -0.0088348388671875, 0.0260772705078125, -0.0299224853515625, -0.0190887451171875, 0.045379638671875, 0.033782958984375, -0